headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 31 points and 12 rebounds in his return, Tyrese Maxey got his first career triple-double and the Philadelphia 76ers held on to beat the Chicago Bulls 108-100 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 31 in his return, Maxey has his first triple-double, Sixers beat Bulls 108-100

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetkounmpo had 34 points, 11 rebounds and four assists and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped a two-game skid with a 118-113 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks snap a 2-game skid with a 118-113 victory over the Nets

headlines.description: — Brandon Miller hit two free throws in the final seconds and finished with 26 points as the Charlotte Hornets snapped an eight-game losing streak with a 113-109 win over the Indiana Pacers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Miller's late free throws help Hornets beat the Pacers 113-109 and snap 8-game skid

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 48 points and the Denver Nuggets never trailed in their 141-111 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores 48 points as Nuggets rout Hawks 141-111

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 34 points, Duncan Robinson had 23 and the Miami Heat stayed hot by beating the Cleveland Cavaliers 122-113 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 34, Robinson adds 23 and Heat beat Cleveland 122-113, only 4th loss for Cavs

headlines.description: — Jalen Suggs scored 14 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter on Sunday night and the Orlando Magic beat the Phoenix Suns 115-110 to remain the NBA's only team unbeaten at home this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suggs scores 26 and Magic turn back Suns for 10th straight win at home

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 21 points, Scotty Pippen Jr. had 14 points and 12 assists and the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies romped to a 140-112 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Grizzlies cruise to 140-112 win over Wizards

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Chris Paul moved into second place on the NBA's career assists list, Victor Wembanyama came back from an injury scare to score 25 points and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 121-116 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama helps Spurs beat Pelicans, 121-116, as Paul moves into second in career assists

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry sunk a 39-foot jumper from nearly halfcourt to beat the third-quarter buzzer and finished with 30 points and eight assists, leading the Golden State Warriors past the Minnesota Timberwolves 114-106 on Sunday night in the teams' second...
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 30 and dishes out eight assists as Warriors beat Timberwolves 114-106

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 31 points, Amen Thompson added 22 and the Houston Rockets defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 117-106 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 31 to lead Rockets past Clippers 117-106

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter had 26 points, including six 3-pointers, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Utah Jazz 141-97 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Huerter's 26 points leads Kings in 141-97 blowout over Jazz

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James sat out the Los Angeles Lakers' 107-98 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday due to left foot soreness, the NBA career scoring leader's first missed game of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James misses 1st game this season, sidelined versus Portland due to left foot soreness
